From a43deda0fae0a38f761c0534cd81043545b2682f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ram <chan2006@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 9 Jul 2026 11:17:52 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add 1-click AWS Connect via CloudFormation cross-account role
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Second, lower-friction path for Brownfield auto-discover, alongside
the CLI (kept for power users / CI pipelines). Uses the industry-
standard pattern (same one Wiz, Orca, Datadog Cloud Security, and
Prisma Cloud use): a CloudFormation Quick-Create Stack URL that
deploys a read-only cross-account IAM role, trust-scoped with a
unique ExternalId to prevent the confused-deputy problem.

- lib/aws-connect/sts.ts: assumeCustomerRole() and
  verifyRoleAssumable(), using ArchAI's own limited AWS identity
  (sts:AssumeRole only, no other permissions of its own — all
  actual read access comes from the role the customer creates and
  controls).
- lib/aws-connect/scanner.ts: server-side AWS discovery using
  assumed credentials. Ports the exact same logic already proven
  live against a real AWS account in archai-cli (per-bucket region
  resolution, distinguishing 'not configured' from genuine access
  errors, per-resource-type resilience).
- app/api/aws-connect/init: generates a per-connection ExternalId
  and the CloudFormation Quick-Create URL.
- app/api/aws-connect/confirm: verifies the pasted-back Role ARN
  is genuinely assumable (real AssumeRole + GetCallerIdentity call)
  before marking the connection active — a bad ARN or mismatched
  ExternalId fails immediately with a clear message rather than
  silently 'succeeding'.
- app/api/aws-connect/scan: assumes the role, scans, and runs the
  exact same Auditor -> Planner -> Engineer -> ADR pipeline as
  every other Brownfield entry point.
- components/brownfield/BrownfieldClient.tsx: new 'Connect AWS
  (1-click)' input option with a 3-step UI (launch stack -> paste
  Role ARN -> run scan).
- package.json: added @aws-sdk/client-sts, client-ec2, client-s3,
  client-rds (verified real, current versions against npm).

Also delivered separately (not part of this repo): a CloudFormation
template (archai-readonly-role.yaml) defining the least-privilege
read-only role, validated with the real cfn-lint tool (installed
and run, not just eyeballed) — caught and fixed a real NoEcho/
Outputs anti-pattern this way.

Needs before this works in production:
1. Run create_aws_connections_table.sql in Supabase (new table).
2. Replace <ARCHAI_AWS_ACCOUNT_ID> in the CFN template with
   NexPlan's real AWS account ID, then host the template file
   publicly (e.g. an S3 bucket with public-read).
3. Create a dedicated IAM user in that AWS account with ONLY
   sts:AssumeRole permission — no other access — and set its
   access key as ARCHAI_AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID / ARCHAI_AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY
   in Vercel env vars, plus ARCHAI_AWS_ACCOUNT_ID and
   ARCHAI_CFN_TEMPLATE_URL (the public template URL from step 2).

Verified: tsc --noEmit clean, next build succeeds (all 3 new
aws-connect routes confirmed in route table), no new lint errors
(same pre-existing no-html-link-for-pages issue, unrelated).
